"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-07-27-historic-river-parade-dion-show-stopper-ignite-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Paris, France (AFP) - A historic boat parade down the River Seine launched the Paris Olympics with spectacular French flair Friday, as the City of Light welcomed the world's greatestathletes for a sporting extravaganza.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.643833955905971e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999964189756619, \"rank\": 1.424423597846855e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 54, \"end\": 65, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 111, \"end\": 117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.73964630269605, \"rank\": 0.33775597272556074, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A show-stopping performance by Celine Dion, a flaming Olympic cauldron lifted into the night sky by hot-air balloon, and a dazzling Eiffel Tower light show brought the curtain down on a four-hour celebration of French culture, history and art.\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 252, \"end\": 263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.083526369537305e-29, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 432, \"end\": 446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Braving torrential rain, some 300,000 people had lined the river banks to cheer on the armada carrying competitors past the city's iconic sights: the Eiffel Tower bearing the five Olympic rings, the Louvre and Notre Dame Cathedral.\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 665, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.6922278218008558, \"rank\": 0.44461110707505247, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wildly ambitious display was the first time the Olympic opening ceremony has been staged outside the main stadium, making it the biggest-ever launch for the \\\"Greatest Show on Earth\\\".\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 885, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But that gamble also made the ceremony hostage to the weather, with spectators, VIPs, and athletes alike drenched or huddling in transparent ponchos.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 1036, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some spectators refused to let the downpour get them down.\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1096, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have got such an adrenaline rush.\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's very exciting,\\\" said Selene Martinez, 42, who had travelled from Mexico for the ceremony.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1161, \"end\": 1167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selene\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.278292690694515e-15, \"text\": \"Selene\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selene\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selene\"}, {\"begin\": 1168, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tippy_Martinez\", \"score\": 0.7379899399963509, \"rank\": 0.3550175899341995, \"text\": \"Martinez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tippy_Martinez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tippy_Martinez\"}, {\"begin\": 1205, \"end\": 1211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"score\": 0.999999817138831, \"rank\": 1.4493602874852886e-07, \"text\": \"Mexico\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But others were less stoic about the heavy rain on the parade, with some leaving the ceremony early to seek shelter.\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a great idea.\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The performances are awesome.\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just wish it wasn't raining,\\\" said Pauline Brett, 69, who had come from Chicago with her family.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1436, \"end\": 1443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9947891333295277, \"rank\": 0.005234783570520376, \"text\": \"Pauline\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 1473, \"end\": 1480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 0.9999379297247672, \"rank\": 6.206093209991364e-05, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the City of Love, the ceremony stressed togetherness and unity in a world that has suffered wars, massacres, and political upheaval since the COVID-delayed Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999211459903895, \"rank\": 7.886022800460643e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Four jets from the French air force display team drew a large pink heart in the Paris sky to set the tone.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1694, \"end\": 1700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.73964630269605, \"rank\": 0.33775597272556074, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1755, \"end\": 1760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.643833955905971e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For just over a fortnight, organisers hope the superhuman performances of stars like gymnast Simone Biles, tennis champion Novak Djokovic or sprinter Noah Lyles will provide the world with much-needed distraction.\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1876, \"end\": 1888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 1933, \"end\": 1943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beach volleyball at the Eiffel Tower, breakdancing in Place de la Concorde, equestrian sport at the Palace of Versailles: 100 years since Paris last staged the Olympics, the city will provide a stunning backdrop to the sport.\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2052, \"end\": 2072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9313557764424182e-17, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 2136, \"end\": 2141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.643833955905971e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I declare open the Games of Paris celebrating the 33rd Olympiad of the modern era,\\\" said President Emmanuel Macron.\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2254, \"end\": 2259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.643833955905971e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2325, \"end\": 2340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a symbol of the Games' message of gender parity, French track legend Marie-Jose Perec and three-time Olympic judo champion Teddy Riner lit the Olympic cauldron together.\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2395, \"end\": 2401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.73964630269605, \"rank\": 0.33775597272556074, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2415, \"end\": 2431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"score\": 0.9999999999295142, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marie-Jose Perec\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\"}, {\"begin\": 2469, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dion closed the show from the first level of the Eiffel Tower, with her first public performance since revealing she was suffering from a rare illness.\", \"from\": 2517, \"to\": 2668, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2683, \"entities\": []}]}"